description: One flower and one bud on one 29.5-cm sequentially blooming inflorescence; dorsal sepal white overlaid light green medially, heavily spotted burgundy, speckled marginally; synsepal white overlaid light green, light burgundy veins, burgundy spots proximal 2/3; petals light green overlaid burgundy except spotted burgundy proximally; pouch 30-degree angle from vertical, light green overlaid burgundy; staminode light green overlaid burgundy; substance medium; texture glossy.

One colorful flower on one unsupported upright 42-cm inflorescence; sepals apple green veined dark green; petals apple green, saturated burgundy spots basal half, overlaid burgundy distal half; pouch apple green, blushed mahogany superior two-thirds; staminode light green marked dark green; substance firm; texture waxy.

Five flowers and five buds on two up to 26-cm upright inflorescences; sepals and petals pink, stippled darker pink distally; lip white, overlaid lavender-pink sidelobe exterior and midlobe tip, ruffled side lobes and midlobe; column white blushed pink, anther cap light yellow; substance hard; texture crystalline.

One well-presented flower on one 16.3-cm inflorescence; dorsal sepal white, green veins, blushed burgundy basally, margins hirsute; synsepal white, green veins; petals chartreuse, green veins, burgundy spots, margins blushed burgundy, hairsute; pouch chartreuse, overlaid brown; staminode pale green, darker green markings centrally; substance medium; texture glossy, pouch waxy.
